cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper is about proposing a new activation function for neural networks and evaluating its performance on various datasets. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, since the paper discusses the performance of the activation function on image classification tasks, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the proposed activation function, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category. The paper's focus on improving the performance of neural networks suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper discusses the use of the proposed activation function in natural language processing tasks, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
